by Wormfodder Delivery » Thu Feb 03, 2022 5:03 am

The problem is mostly that people use template nations without putting any effort in to make them actually good.

Like, you can take a basic concept and still make it interesting by putting in quality.
Or you make a concept that is weird enough so it is still interesting.
Optimally, you do both the unusual concept and making it good.

But those who do the template nations don't do either. And it mostly will lead to them being forgotten.
Like, I personally can't keep most of the authoritarian americas apart from each other, they all blend in together in my head like a big, "OH LOOK I AM SO COOL" sludge. Same for the generic communist nations, the barely different eaglelands, the standard european monarchy, the generic authoritarian dictatorships, the space empires with a 1800's mindset, etc. If you are one of those, you honestly can just stop actually writing, cause none of it is gonna be remembered when it joins the pile of generic sludge.

To those who I am reffering to there, stop wasting everyones time with having to deal with your unimaginative, creatively bankrupt, generic nation that won't leave a lasting impact. Noone wants to read your nationwanks.

-Goguryeo wrote:Cliche: Using Nationstates to post your bogstandard PolWank.


This

I largely based GWO on my RL beliefs with some changes to account for the fact that (most) of the people in it didn't grow up in the US like I did, but I still also include plenty of social ills, problems, inefficiencies, and outright horror stories of government overreach- no ideology or governing style will solve all issues, it's simply a matter of choosing which ones you'd rather have to accept. Sure, back when I used to RP, GWO went around smashing communist countries to the point where there wasn't an organized left-wing alliance in II, and that was pretty cool and in line with my ideals, but I saw the real human cost for both the countries being invaded and the GWO's own people as an excellent subject matter for writing. It kind of loops around to a post I made earlier, where a lot of democratic nations like to RP as if their social programs all work, and there's also conveniently no real opposition politically to the whims of their leader, who also never seems to leave office! And, despite losing hundreds of thousands of troops in a totally unjustifiable war and a lack of a major military culture, there's no shortage of volunteers, so even though "conscription can be used," it conveniently never has to be!

-Goguryeo wrote:Cliche: Using Nationstates to post your bogstandard PolWank.

That is a problem with a lot of fiction, that the authors personal politics are inserted as something unfathomable right and the opposing ones are depicted as the worst beings imaginable.
This is what led me to the decision to make the Wormfodder Delivery Service into something that has little relation to my personal outlook. Even if I accidently let some of my views sicker through and tend to sometimes do some jokes about them.

Personally, I find it more interesting if one were to make the ideals one finds abhorrent irl into the good guys ones and the ones they identify with into the evil antagonists one. Altough I personally am currently not exactly capable of writing that. Except maybe as a piece of humor-writing, but that would defeat the point of actually analyzing the other viewpoints.
